setClonePtnOrient(25.10)                              setClonePtnOrient(25.10)

Name
       setClonePtnOrient  - Changes the orientation of the specified partition
       clone

Syntax
       setClonePtnOrient

       [-help]

       <name>

       {R0 R90 R180 R270 MX MX90 MY MY90}

       Changes the orientation of the specified partition clone.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each setClonePtnOrient parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setClonePtnOrient.

       <name> Specifies  the name of the partition clone whose orientation has
              to be changed.

              Data_type: (hinst), required

       {R0 R90 R180 R270 MX MX90 MY MY90}
              Specifies the orientation. The orientation can  be  one  of  the
              following:

              * R0

              * MY

              * MX

              * R180

              * MX90

              * R90

              * R270

              * MY90

              Data_type: enum, required

Example
       The  following command sets the orientation of the partition clone name
       TDSP_ARB_C1 to R270:

       setClonePtnOrient TDSP_ARB_C1 R270

